# Finder/iCloud-style duplicate files ("name 2.ext", "name 3.ext", …).
# These get created on the maintainer's Mac and were twice swept into
# commits by `git add -A` (the 20 MB essc-2025 2.mp4 and a stray
# conference-media 2.njk). Ignore the whole class as a mechanical guard
# — no legitimate repo file uses a " <digit>.ext" suffix. (Still eyeball
# `git status` before committing, per CLAUDE.md §8.)
* [0-9].*
